@bff_url = http://localhost:5224
@keycloak_url = https://identity.alexbartleynees.com

### 1. Test BFF is running
GET {{bff_url}}/
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Check Duende BFF Management Endpoints (should return 401 if not authenticated)
GET {{bff_url}}/bff/user
Accept: application/json
X-CSRF: 1

###

### 3. Test Login Endpoint (Duende BFF provides this)
GET {{bff_url}}/bff/login
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Test Logout Endpoint
GET {{bff_url}}/bff/logout
Accept: application/json

###

### 5. Test Protected API Route (proxied to backend)
# This should require authentication and forward token
GET {{bff_url}}/api/suggestions
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Check if backend service is reachable directly (bypass BFF)
# This tests if your starter-service is running
GET http://starter-service:8080/api/test
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. Test Keycloak is running
GET {{keycloak_url}}/realms/production/.well-known/openid-configuration
Accept: application/json

###

### 8. Test Keycloak (Development realm)
GET {{keycloak_url}}/realms/development/.well-known/openid-configuration
Accept: application/json

###
